column5: I spent this past weekend up at a camp near Parry Sound.  I had never been there before and didn't really know what to expect fishing wise.  I figured it would be smallmouth and pike mostly as the lake seemed fairly deep along the shorelines.  I managed to get a canoe for a few hours so me and a friend went out for an hour or so just around the camp.  First couple casts I got this nice largemouth off a submerged tree on a spinnerbait.  My scale said she was right on 5 pounds, she was a fatty.    My friend got a nice 3 pound smallmouth off the same tree and it was his first bass so he was pretty pumped.  That was all the fishing I got in for the weekend, but i'm glad I went out.  And I would love to fish that area more, what a beautiful place this time of year.
WTG evster  Real chunky LMB An hour well spent on the water Thanks for sharing Leechman
Nice fish. What is the camp name?
very nice bass. So many spots to try up there it would take a lifetime
